<item>
            <title>[DERBY-2150] Reduce use of synchronized collections in GenericLanguageConnectionContext</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-2150</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In org.apache.derby.impl.sql.conn.GenericLanguageConnectionContext, it is probably safe to replace some of the synchronized collections with unsynchronized ones. This should be investigated, and the unnecessary synchronization should be removed. See discussion here: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/Use-of-synchronized-containers-in-engine-code-tf2754469.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/Use-of-synchronized-containers-in-engine-code-tf2754469.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
